# Ladybird Project Overview

## About Ladybird

[Ladybird](https://ladybird.org) is a truly independent web browser using a novel engine based on web standards.

**Status:** Pre-alpha (suitable for developers only)

**Goal:** Build a complete, usable browser for the modern web

## Architecture

### Multi-Process Architecture
- **Main UI Process**: User interface
- **WebContent Processes**: Renderer per tab (sandboxed)
- **ImageDecoder Process**: Image decoding (isolated for security)
- **RequestServer Process**: Network connections (isolated for robustness)

Each tab has its own renderer process, sandboxed from the system for security against malicious content.

## Core Libraries (Inherited from SerenityOS)

### Web Technologies
- **LibWeb**: Web rendering engine
- **LibJS**: JavaScript engine
- **LibWasm**: WebAssembly implementation
- **LibIDL**: IDL parser and bindings generator

### Networking & Security
- **LibCrypto/LibTLS**: Cryptography primitives and TLS
- **LibHTTP**: HTTP/1.1 client
- **LibDNS**: DNS resolution
- **LibWebSocket**: WebSocket implementation

### Media & Graphics
- **LibGfx**: 2D graphics, image decoding and rendering
- **LibMedia**: Audio and video playback

### System & Utilities
- **LibCore**: Event loop and OS abstraction layer
- **LibIPC**: Inter-process communication
- **LibFileSystem**: File system utilities
- **LibThreading**: Threading utilities
- **LibMain**: Main entry point abstraction

### Data & Utilities
- **AK**: Application Kit - fundamental data structures and utilities
- **LibCompress**: Compression (Deflate, Gzip, Zlib)
- **LibUnicode**: Unicode and locale support
- **LibTextCodec**: Text encoding/decoding
- **LibURL**: URL parsing and manipulation
- **LibRegex**: Regular expressions
- **LibXML**: XML parsing
- **LibDiff**: Diff algorithm

### Development
- **LibTest**: Testing framework
- **LibDevTools**: Browser DevTools implementation
- **LibSyntax**: Syntax highlighting

